title: Whincup impresses as Ferrari dip into ‘fours’
text:
Bathurst 12 Hour: Toni Vilander tops Practice 2 as Jamie Whincup impresses February 3, 2017 11:11am @willdale956 Source: FOX SPORTS JAMIE Whincup took just a handful of laps to answer any questions about whether his ability in a Supercar would translate to a GT3 car. 
It was his teammate Toni Vilander that topped Practice 2 at the Bathurst 12 Hour in their No. 88 Ferrari 488, but Whincup’s best was just a few tenths shy of the factory driver’s time. 
Whincup dropped in a 2m04.84s on his seventh flying lap, quicker than his Supercars lap record at Mount Panorama despite encountering traffic in the final sector. Sector data shows his theoretical best lap, adding a quicker final sector from a later lap, would have a 2m03.936s. 
Just as impressive was his longtime sparring partner Mark Winterbottom, who put the No. 60 BMW M6 GT3 second fastest just 0.18 of a second down on the Ferrari. 
PRACTICE 1: Ingall fastest early at Bathurst 12 Hour 
The BMW had earlier triggered the only red flag of the session, Steven Richards slowing on his way up the hill on the car’s out lap, returning to the session soon after its resumption. 
The two Australian flag-liveried Jamec Pem Audi R8s were next in third and fourth. The No. 75 all-international car of ex-F1 racers Markus Winkelhock and Robin Frijns with Frank Stippler pipped the No. 74 that Garth Tander will share with Christopher Mies and Christopher Haase, Tander getting away with a quick spin in the early minutes. 
2015 winners Nissan were next up, Katsumasa Chiyo popping in a lap as the chequered flag waved to move the No. 23 GT-R up to fifth place. 
The No. 7 BMW M6 that topped the opening session cruised to sixth in the all-in Practice 2, ex-F1 racer Timo Glock doing the honours, while Maro Engel put the No. 22 Mercedes-AMG GT3 he will share with Shane van Gisbergen and Craig Baird into eighth place. 
There was one small drama as the session ended for the No. 90 MARC Cars BMW M6, the metallic green machine rolling to a stop at Skyline on its in-lap. 
The reason? Out of fuel... Stopped in for a chat. #B12hr pic.twitter.com/WYCllodRKq — Tori Martin (@Tiri_Trouble) February 2, 2017 
The cars will next hit the track at 12:35pm AEDT for their third of four practice sessions on the opening day.
